videoframeSigmonVm0007MIB.description: This MIB describes the device specific objects of the VM0007 Transfer Switch module, and augments MIB-2, VF-GENERIC, and VF-SIGMON in the identification of this Videoframe Systems managed device. This module will be extended or modified as required. Videoframe Systems reserves the right to make changes in specification and other information contained in this document without prior notice. vfProductsVM0007Reg.name: vfProductsVM0007Reg
vfProductsVM0007Reg.description: Videoframe VM0007 A/V Transfer Switch Module.

vm0007Table.name: vm0007Table
vm0007Table.description: Each row contains information about one VM0007 A/V Transfer Switch module in the managed VF200 frame.

vm0007Entry.name: vm0007Entry
vm0007Entry.description: A VM0007 A/V Transfer Switch module entry.

vm0007SlotNumber.name: vm0007SlotNumber
vm0007SlotNumber.description: The slot that this entry represents.

vm0007Active.name: vm0007Active
vm0007Active.description: Indicates whether this entry is active (this module is in this slot).

vm0007Locate.name: vm0007Locate
vm0007Locate.description: Controls the locate indicator on the module and indicates its current state. Set to flash (1) to cause the locate LED on the front of the module to begin flashing. Set to off to stop flashing.

vm0007VideoSignalSwitchState.name: vm0007VideoSignalSwitchState
vm0007VideoSignalSwitchState.description: Controls the the video signal switch on the module and indicates its current state.

vm0007TransferSwitchAlarmAck.name: vm0007TransferSwitchAlarmAck
vm0007TransferSwitchAlarmAck.description: Set to acknowledge (3) to acknowledge a triggered transfer switch alarm. This will acknowledge both the transferSwitchActivatedAlarm and the transferSwitchNormalAlarm. With Auto Re-Arm off, one of each alarm will be allowed between acknowledges.

vm0007CPUOverride.name: vm0007CPUOverride
vm0007CPUOverride.description: Set to 'on' to ignore GPI inputs on the module back panel and put the switch completely under SNMP or network API control.

vm0007VideoSource1Name.name: vm0007VideoSource1Name
vm0007VideoSource1Name.description: The name of the signal connected to the 'S1' video input.

vm0007VideoSource1Description.name: vm0007VideoSource1Description
vm0007VideoSource1Description.description: Descriptive identification of the signal connected to the 'S1' video input.

vm0007VideoSource2Name.name: vm0007VideoSource2Name
vm0007VideoSource2Name.description: The name of the signal connected to the 'S2' video input.

vm0007VideoSource2Description.name: vm0007VideoSource2Description
vm0007VideoSource2Description.description: Descriptive identification of the signal connected to the 'S2' video input.

vm0007VideoDest1Name.name: vm0007VideoDest1Name
vm0007VideoDest1Name.description: The name of the destination for the 'D1' video output.

vm0007VideoDest1Description.name: vm0007VideoDest1Description
vm0007VideoDest1Description.description: Descriptive identification of the destination for the 'D1' video output.

vm0007VideoDest2Name.name: vm0007VideoDest2Name
vm0007VideoDest2Name.description: The name of the destination for the 'D2' video output.

vm0007VideoDest2Description.name: vm0007VideoDest2Description
vm0007VideoDest2Description.description: Descriptive identification of the destination for the 'D2' video output.

vm0007AudioChannelTable.name: vm0007AudioChannelTable
vm0007AudioChannelTable.description: Each row contains information about one audio channel of one VM0007 A/V Transfer Switch module in the managed VF200 frame.

vm0007AudioChannelEntry.name: vm0007AudioChannelEntry
vm0007AudioChannelEntry.description: An A/V Transfer Switch module audio channel entry.

vm0007AudioChannelSlotNumber.name: vm0007AudioChannelSlotNumber
vm0007AudioChannelSlotNumber.description: The frame slot number that this entry represents.

vm0007AudioChannelNumber.name: vm0007AudioChannelNumber
vm0007AudioChannelNumber.description: The channel within the module to which this signal is connected.

vm0007AudioChannelSwitchState.name: vm0007AudioChannelSwitchState
vm0007AudioChannelSwitchState.description: Controls the audio signal switch for this channel and indicates its current state.

vm0007AudioChanSource1Name.name: vm0007AudioChanSource1Name
vm0007AudioChanSource1Name.description: The name of the signal connected to S1-An for this channel.

vm0007AudioChanSource1Description.name: vm0007AudioChanSource1Description
vm0007AudioChanSource1Description.description: Descriptive identification of the signal connected to S1-An for this channel.

vm0007AudioChanSource2Name.name: vm0007AudioChanSource2Name
vm0007AudioChanSource2Name.description: The name of the signal connected to S2-An for this channel.

vm0007AudioChanSource2Description.name: vm0007AudioChanSource2Description
vm0007AudioChanSource2Description.description: Descriptive identification of the signal connected to S2-An for this channel.

vm0007AudioChanDest1Name.name: vm0007AudioChanDest1Name
vm0007AudioChanDest1Name.description: The name of the signal connected to D1-An for this channel.

vm0007AudioChanDest1Description.name: vm0007AudioChanDest1Description
vm0007AudioChanDest1Description.description: Descriptive identification of the signal connected to D1-An for this channel.

vm0007AudioChanDest2Name.name: vm0007AudioChanDest2Name
vm0007AudioChanDest2Name.description: The name of the signal connected to D1-An for this channel.

vm0007AudioChanDest2Description.name: vm0007AudioChanDest2Description
vm0007AudioChanDest2Description.description: Descriptive identification of the signal connected to D1-An for this channel.

transferSwitchActivatedAlarm.name: transferSwitchActivatedAlarm
transferSwitchActivatedAlarm.description: An A/V Transfer Switch was switched to crossover (backup) mode.

transferSwitchNormalAlarm.name: transferSwitchNormalAlarm
transferSwitchNormalAlarm.description: An A/V Transfer Switch was switched to straight through (normal) mode.
